## 5) Form submission flow to MongoDB

## Step 1: Create draft / initial request

`POST /api/requests`

Request body:

```json
{
  "requestType": "RTP",
  "routingType": "GCPC",
  "requestorId": "665f9b0c9f7e1e6a6cc6a001",
  "companyId": "665f9b0c9f7e1e6a6cc6a010",
  "projectId": "665f9b0c9f7e1e6a6cc6a020",
  "acknowledgement": false,
  "formData": {
    "clientName": "ABC Client",
    "descriptionOfMatters": "Registration of Tender List",
    "requestTitle": "Tender Registration for Phase 2",
    "tenderClosingDate": "2026-04-10T00:00:00.000Z",
    "specialProjectWaiver": false
  }
}
```

Server action:
- generate `requestNo`
- set `status = "New"`
- create first event in `request_events`

## Step 2: Upload files

`POST /api/requests/:id/files`

Request body:

```json
{
  "files": [
    {
      "fileName": "Tender-Form.pdf",
      "url": "https://res.cloudinary.com/.../Tender-Form.pdf",
      "mimeType": "application/pdf",
      "sizeBytes": 452311,
      "cloudinaryId": "gcp-central/req-123/tender-form"
    }
  ]
}
```

Server validation:
- max files per request = 10
- max file size = 10MB (or project-configurable if policy changes)

## Step 3: Autosave edits

`PATCH /api/requests/:id`

Request body:

```json
{
  "formData": {
    "requestTitle": "Updated title"
  }
}
```

## Step 4: Final submit

`POST /api/requests/:id/submit`

Rules:
- required form fields must pass validation
- `acknowledgement` must be `true`
- attachments required by form type must exist
- set `timeline.submittedAt`

## Step 5: Verification / review workflow updates

Examples:
- verifier approve -> `status = "Verified"`
- verifier asks changes -> `status = "Rework"`
- engagement created -> `status = "R"`, `engagementRound = 1..n`
- review result updates `reviewCode` + `outcomeCode`
- close request -> `status = "Closed"` (or `FR` where applicable)

Every transition writes one `request_events` record.

## 6) Recommended Mongoose implementation pattern

1. Parent model: `Request` with `discriminatorKey: "requestType"`.
2. Child models: `RTPRequest`, `PBLRequest`, `JVPRequest`, `CAARequest`, etc.
3. Keep common fields only in parent model.
4. Keep form-only fields in discriminator models.
5. Keep workflow/audit in separate collections (`request_events`, `engagement_sessions`, `summary_review_reports`).

## 7) Minimal validation checklist

- `requestType`, `routingType`, `requestorId`, `companyId`, `projectId` required.
- `requestTitle` max 100 chars for RTP.
- conditional required:
  - `tenderClosingDate` required when RTP matters = Tender List.
- file constraints:
  - max 10 files
  - max 10MB each
- before final submit:
  - `acknowledgement === true`
  - required fields complete

---

This model gives you:
- clean form extensibility
- BRD-compatible statuses/outcomes
- strong audit and SLA tracking
- reliable API-based submission flow to MongoDB.
